      "content": "that's a pretty big pivot from an audit finding to it being a \"deliberate maintenance window.\" \n\nim worried that if an investigative reporter looks at the actual logs and sees nobody was actually performing maintenance, we'll get caught in a flat-out lie about it being a \"planned\" event. would it be safer to say it was a \"temporary synchronization discrepancy\" during an optimization process? something that sounds technical and complex so they don't dig deeper, but doesn't involve saying we planned for the data to be out there?",
